  <Docs>
    <summary>Holds options for creating an XPS document.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKDocumentXpsOptions` is a value type that controls how an XPS document is produced by the SkiaSharp document API. Pass an instance to the XPS document creation method to control the output resolution and PNG usage.

Because this is a struct, no disposal is required.

## Examples

```csharp
using var stream = new SKFileWStream("output.xps");
var options = new SKDocumentXpsOptions
{
    DPI = 300,
    AllowNoPngs = false,
};
using var document = SKDocument.CreateXps(stream, options.DPI);
using var canvas = document.BeginPage(595, 842);
canvas.Clear(SKColors.White);
document.EndPage();
document.Close();
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
